This paper deals with the analysis of coverage probability in wireless communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the use of statistical methods to model the interference, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NI). The study of correlated interferers is a topic related to signal processing (cs.SI). The use of special functions to simplify the coverage probability expressions is a topic related to mathematical analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the comparison of coverage probability in different scenarios involves game theory concepts (cs.GT).
